genera, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1878" box="[511,646,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Cardiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,646,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Cardiodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by its large size, long wings most often with whitish spots in both sexes, male FW venation (Wshaped harp veins, mirror incomplete generally elongated longitudinally), and male genitalia (pseudepiphallic dorso-lateral ridges, posterior apex of pseudepiphallus more or less spoon-like).
